  | The grep command in Unix/Linux is a powerful tool used for searching    |
  | and manipulating text patterns within files.                            |
  | By default, grep displays the entire line which has the matched string. |
  | We can make the grep to display only the matched string by using the -o |
  | option.                                                                 |
  |    [1;33mgrep -o "pattern" filename   [0m                                        |
